    "Following is the mathematical expression for random sampling with temperature [50],P (w) = exp (P (w)/τ) w ′ exp (P (w ′)/τ)(4)where:τ: temperature parameter controlling distribution w ′ exp (P (w ′)/τ): normalization factorTable 1 provides an overview of the hyperparameters employed during the fine-tuning of our models, including details on class type and the tokenizer used.",
    "The CISO LLM received a prompt accompanied by PDF files, serving the purpose of configuring the RAG, whereas LLM2 received the prompt along with a cybersecurity handbook.",
    "The bounded rationality of this LLM, enhanced by RAG, is defined by its specific pre-training on organizational knowledge, complemented by dynamic retrieval of relevant, up-to-date organizational documents.",
    "While its decision-making and outputs are tailored to the scope of its initial training data and programmed understanding of organizational roles, infrastructure, and objectives, the RAG component allows it to incorporate the latest organizational documents and data into its narrative generation.",
